  "prompt": "How do fund of funds (FOF) strategies function?",
  "response": "Fund of Funds (FOF) strategies function through the following key mechanisms:\n\n1. Investment Approach:\n- Invest in multiple underlying mutual funds, hedge funds, or other investment vehicles\n- Diversify across different fund managers, asset classes, and investment strategies\n- Provide broader market exposure through a single investment vehicle\n\n2. Selection Process:\n- Carefully evaluate and select underlying funds based on:\n- Performance history\n- Management expertise\n- Risk profile\n- Investment strategy\n- Fees and expenses\n\n3. Asset Allocation:\n- Spread investments across various:\n- Geographic regions\n- Sectors\n- Investment styles\n- Risk levels\n\n4. Types of FOF:\n- Multi-manager funds\n- Target-date retirement funds\n- Alternative investment funds\n- Global/international funds\n\n5. Management Strategies:\n- Active management: Actively selecting and rebalancing underlying funds\n- Passive management: Tracking broader market indices or specific themes\n\n6. Potential Benefits:\n- Enhanced diversification\n- Professional fund selection\n- Reduced individual fund risk\n- Simplified investment process\n\n7. Considerations:\n- Additional layer of fees\n- Potential performance drag\n- Complexity in performance tracking",
